rComments: This class is really hard. She first assumed that everyone knows the background but she was better later. I dropped the class because i couldnt follow but she tries quite hard. She "wondered" why more people sit in the class than are registered...given that there are no young female faculty in CS- duh!

She is quite disorganized with the lectures and puts a lot of presure on the students to learn on their own. She assumes everyone is a genius and/or are really exposed to the keywords. She is quite enthusiastic about the subject though, which is a plus. I wish she'd pay less attention to her appearance and more to organizing her course.

Prof Vasudevan covered topics that were out of the scope of the textbook but i was impressed with how she kept it up through the semester. She is very energetic and tries very hard to make people learn.

She covered topics that were practical and relevant. She has tons of enthusiasm and is a great communicator. The homeworks and midterms became much better after she assessed the level of the class. I got an internship in NVIDIA because of the stuff i learnt in her class. Altogether, good stuff! (Also, eye candy ;))

Had her for her first semester at UIUC. Makes tons of errors during class (I don't think she knows the material), homeworks take too long are are often unclear/wrong, and the midterm had nothing to do with what we covered prior to it. Avoid like the plague!
